Updating this fork to a new release of Lua is a manual process.
This document describes how to get started on that.

Updating the code
=================

0. Note on the test suite: this fork keeps the official tests in tests/,
   whereas upstream ships them in testes/. When refreshing, extract
   upstream's testes/* into this repo's tests/ (contents stay verbatim;
   only the directory name differs). The $Id: testes/... $ tags inside
   the files are upstream's own and are left untouched.
1. Replace the src folder with a clean copy of Lua.
2. Reapply the one modification.
   - The authoritative set is enforced by scripts/verify-stock.sh, which on
     every CI run diffs the vendored core against stock Lua and asserts that
     exactly one source file differs: luac.c. Diff it against the clean copy
     from step 1 to see the change.
   - luac.c: the assert-safe bytecode-listing rework. Stock luac hoists
     GETARG_* into locals, which trips lua_assert on opcodes lacking those
     argument formats under -DLUAI_ASSERT.

Testing
=======

Since the vendored core is verbatim stock, the interpreter needs no special
care beyond the official suite (see CONTRIBUTING.md). To exercise the
internals with assertions on, add the LUAI_ASSERT compiler flag:

    MYCFLAGS=-DLUAI_ASSERT

In Lua ≤ 5.4.3, luac had a bug and did not work correctly with the
assertions. This includes the luac.c rework noted above. If this isn't
fixed yet, you may need to fix luac.c (see commit 1a1fefac) or just disable
the assertions in that file with a `#undef LUAI_ASSERT` at the top of the
file.
